main event: Multiple sightings of unidentified flying objects reported in Olean, New York from February 11 to March 1, 1953.
interesting points: A blue-white object was sighted circling at altitudes of 6,900 to 7,200 feet., The Object was observed for varying lengths of time ranging from 30 seconds to 25 minutes., Observers included qualified military personnel and local news reporters., Several reports concluded that insufficient data for evaluation left open the possibility of astronomical bodies like Venus., There were eight sightings reported in total during this period, indicating a potential increase in unusual aerial activity.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects of various colors and shapes, including a silver disc and a blue-white object
witness description: Qualified ground observers and local photographers
